OL,3,CAlderney's leading politician says
OL,4,Creview into economic deal is 'sensible'
OL,6,FAlderney's leading politician says
OL,7,Fit's "sensible" for there to be a
OL,8,Freview into a post-war financial
OL,9,Fagreement between Alderney and
OL,10,FGuernsey.
OL,12,FBill Abel, Chair of the Policy and
OL,13,FFinance Committee, told ITV News that
OL,14,Freviewing the agreement is timely
OL,15,Fgiven the #24 million deficit faced by
OL,16,Fthe States of Guernsey.
OL,18,FThe current agreement, put in place in
OL,19,F1948, states that Guernsey funds
OL,20,FAlderney's key services, in return for
OL,21,Fthe island's income tax revenue.
